---
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';

const pageTitle = 'Best Monitor Riser with Storage for Desk 2026';
const pageDescription = 'Honest review of monitor stands with drawer storage. Lift your screen to eye level and declutter your desk in one move.';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription} />
    <style>
      main { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: #333; }
      h1 { color: #232f3e; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
      .meta { color: #666; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
      .product-box { background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 8px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
      .product-box h2 { margin-top: 0; }
      .product-box ul { padding-left: 1.2rem; }
      .btn { display: inline-block; background: #ff9900; color: #000; padding: 12px 24px; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
      .btn:hover { background: #e68a00; }
      .disclaimer { font-size: 0.8rem; color: #888; margin-top: 3rem; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 1rem; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <h1>Best Monitor Riser with Storage</h1>
      <div class="meta">Updated May 2026 · Under $35</div>

      <p>A monitor should sit at eye level. Most desks are too low, forcing you to look down and hunch. A riser fixes your posture instantly — and the storage underneath hides the mess of cables, pens, and sticky notes that kill productivity.</p>

      <div class="product-box">
        <h2>🏆 Monitor Riser with Pull-Out Drawer</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>3.9-inch lift</strong> — brings 24-27" monitors to ergonomic eye level</li>
          <li><strong>Pull-out drawer</strong> — stores keyboard, mouse, notebook when not in use</li>
          <li><strong>Side phone/tablet slot</strong> — keeps secondary screen visible</li>
          <li><strong>Sturdy MDF + metal legs</strong> — supports up to 33 lbs, no wobble</li>
          <li><strong>Cable management cutout</strong> — route wires through the back, not around</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="https://www.amazon.com/s?k=monitor+riser+with+drawer&tag=toolwise20-20" class="btn" target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored">Check Current Price on Amazon</a>
      </div>

      <h3>Why a riser beats a stack of textbooks</h3>
      <p>Books slide, sag, and look unprofessional on video calls. A dedicated riser gives you a flat, stable surface with enough clearance underneath to stash your keyboard and reclaim desk space. The drawer version is especially useful for standing desk converters — when you raise the desk, the drawer moves with it.</p>

      <h3>Who should buy it</h3>
      <p>Anyone with a fixed-height desk, dual-monitor users who need alignment, and minimalists who want a clean surface for photos and video calls. Combine it with our recommended laptop stand, monitor light bar, and USB-C hub, and you have a complete professional workstation for under $200 total.</p>

      <div class="disclaimer">
        Disclosure: As an Amazon Associate I earn from qualifying purchases. This review is based on independent research and reader feedback.
      </div>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>